{
  "text": "After collection blood was stored at 4 \u2022 C. Serum was separated within 24 h and stored at \u221220 \u2022 C until assayed. Serum IgG antibody levels were measured to the 7 vaccine pneumococcal polysaccharides 4, 6B, 9V, 14, 18C, 19F and 23F. All sera were assayed in the laboratory for infectious diseases of the National Institute for Public Health and the Environment in Bilthoven with ELISA using double adsorption with cell wall polysaccharide and 22F polysaccharide [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
